# Cursor rules → defer to AGENTS.md

`AGENTS.md` at the repo root is the single source of truth. Read it before acting.
These bullets are a summary; on any conflict, `AGENTS.md` wins.

- Monorepo: backend in `apps/api` (FastAPI), frontend in `apps/web` (Next.js App Router + TS + Tailwind).
- Stay inside the current build slice (see `AGENTS.md` §0/§1). Ask the team before adding any feature, page, endpoint, or dependency.
- The API contract lives ONLY in `apps/api/src/models/schemas.py`. The frontend mirrors it in `apps/web/lib/api.ts` — keep both in sync, never invent a second shape.
- Follow existing patterns in the file you edit. No unrelated refactors.
- Every external call (LLM, DB, network) must have a fallback so the demo path never crashes.
- `apps/web` UI follows the `ui-ux-system` skill (`AGENTS.md` §8): token classes only (tokens in `apps/web/app/globals.css`, the one place to change the look), import primitives from `apps/web/components/ui`, dark mode by `.dark` class — no raw hex or per-element `dark:`.
- Before commit: `cd apps/api && make check` and `cd apps/web && npm run build` must pass. Use Conventional Commits, small PRs, keep `main` deployable.
- When unsure, stop and ask a human rather than guessing.
